# SSOT / RTL To Signoff

For real RTL-to-signoff or SSOT-to-signoff work, use `.cursor/skills/rtl-to-signoff/`.

Rules:

- Use the `ssot-to-signoff` profile when the work starts from requirements or needs SSOT generation before DV/EDA closure.
- `ssot-gen` must run through `src/headless_workflow.py --stages ssot-gen` in Cursor, or the runtime `/to-ssot` / `/grill-me` / `/verify-ssot` surfaces outside Cursor.
- Do not bypass `req/approval_manifest.json`, semantic questions, or human gates by editing SSOT YAML directly.
- DV stages must delegate to `WorkflowStageEngine.run_stage()` or `src/headless_workflow.py --stages pipeline`.
- EDA stages must delegate to workflow command scripts such as `workflow/syn/scripts/auto_syn.sh`.
- Do not use disk-check-only scripts as final signoff gates when a common-engine stage exists.
- Treat `STAGE_MANIFEST.json` as the Cursor routing table: stage id, owner workflow, slash surface, invocation type, and evidence paths.
- Stop on `blocked` or `human_gate`; route to the owner workflow instead of patching evidence.
- Treat `sim/simulation_quality.json` as sim-debug-owned generated evidence. Regenerate it via `sim-debug` or `workflow/sim_debug/scripts/check_simulation_quality.py`; do not hand-edit it.
- Regenerate `verify/cursor_rtl_to_signoff_summary.json` by rerunning the runner. Do not edit it directly.
